// Syllogistic Logic: Socrates is Mortal
// ==============================================================================
// This file demonstrates a classic Aristotelian syllogism.
//
// Key Concepts:
// 1. Categorical Statements: "All Men are Mortal".
// 2. Sequential Reasoning: Using ##seq markers to order the logical flow.
// 3. Deductive Inference: Deriving specific truths from general laws.
// ==============================================================================

@version:"1.0.0"
$$group:logical_inference

// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Premise 1 (Minor Premise)
// Logic: "Socrates is a Man."
// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
##seq:1
!Assert {
  <Socrates> [is_a] <Man>
} @1.0

// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Premise 2 (Major Premise)
// Logic: "All Men are Mortal."
// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
##seq:2
!Assert {
  <AllMen> [are] <Mortal>
} @1.0

// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Conclusion (Inference)
// Goal: Verify if Socrates is Mortal based on the premises.
// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
##seq:3
~temp:0.1 // Low temperature for strict logic
!Query {
  <Socrates> [is] <Mortal>
} @0.99

// Logic Flow:
// 1. Socrates -> is_a -> Man
// 2. Man (AllMen) -> are -> Mortal
// 3. Therefore, Socrates -> is -> Mortal